# Package versions stay aligned

All workspace packages share one version. Current: **0.1.3**.

When bumping a version (release, publish, or new package), update **every** `package.json` `version` field in the monorepo to the same value:

| Package | Path |
|---------|------|
| CLI (`create-tawny`) | `apps/cli/package.json` |
| Web app | `apps/web/package.json` |
| UI package | `packages/ui/package.json` |
| Art template | `templates/art/package.json` |
| Dev template | `templates/dev/package.json` |

Do not leave packages on older versions (e.g. `0.1.0` / `0.0.0`) after a bump. The root `package.json` has no `version` (private workspace) — leave it without one.

New packages under `apps/`, `packages/`, or `templates/` must start at the current shared version, not `0.0.0` or `0.1.0`.
